    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="945"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d945">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13610.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Special Agent <persName type="to">Canova</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 2, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>You are instructed informally to bring to the attention of the Convention the
                    following paraphrase of telegram No. 311 which <pb facs="0733" n="617"
                        xml:id="pg_617"/> the Department sent to the Brazilian Minister on November
                    1, 10 p.m.</p>
                <p>[Text of paraphrase.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
